История железнодорожного вокзала Душанбе начинается с 1936 года. Первый поезд прибыл в Сталинабад из Москвы 29 декабря 1950 года. Новый вокзал был возведён в начале 60-х годов и работает до сих пор. В 1962 году из Ташкента в Душанбе, поступил первый тепловоз ТЭ2 (тепловоз с электрической передачей), который выпускался в Харькове с 1948 по 1955 годы.

История железнодорожного вокзала Душанбе начинается с 1936 года. Первый поезд прибыл в Сталинабад из Москвы 29 декабря 1950 года. Новый вокзал был возведён в начале 60-х годов и работает до сих пор. В 1962 году из Ташкента в Душанбе, поступил первый тепловоз ТЭ2 (тепловоз с электрической передачей), который выпускался в Харькове с 1948 по 1955 годы.
One of the best mosques to perform your salahs if you are at downtown area. It has got so many rooms, so even at Jum'a prayers you will surely find a place to pray.
It's usually called Madrassah. Quite Spacious and comfortable. Car Parking is a major problem for this mosque.
Beautiful mosque
Масчиди чомеъ ба номи Хочи Яъкуб ки аз чониби Президенти Чумхури мухтарам Эмомали Рахмон ва собик раиси шахр мухтарам Махмадсаид Убайдуллоев сохта шудааст..))
Очень красиво и  захватывающие место .
Were impressed by Buddha statutue and the princess 👸 skeleton in embryonic pose. Russian/English speaking guide is included in ticket price, closed on Mondays.

Tajikistan is a country, where Zoroastrian, Buddhist, Hellenistic, Islamic and unique Pamir cultures had been developing for thousands of years. Numerous archaeological and natural findings gathered in the Museum of Antiquities of Tajikistan in Dushanbe are the evidence of this abundance of cultures on the Tajik land. Established 1934.
Gr8 antiques
Interesting exhibition. Doesn't have explanation on every exhibitis.
Great museum but get a guide to make the most of it

It was so nice with warm welcome to guests. Food from Tajikistan is always a sign of taste. Atmosphere when I was there in 2005 I like it much, now not sure how it would be but still whatever it is will be better than most of the places. Hope to that again.
Very beautiful atmosphere inside. You can find different art patterns. Price was relatively high. It is really big inside.
Best to go for lunch. Good traditional food and nice atmosphere. Service is fast and food is relatively good, although at a higher side for Dushanbe. A landmark of Dushanbe.

I think this in past famous "Choichona"=Tea House is currently giving up, quality of foods are not the same

Nevertheless I lake this Tea House for its handcrafted decorations, for its locale, for its spirit
Not so much good food but location and atomoshphere is the best .

Здание госбанка советской эпохи перешедший правоприемнику, Национальному Банку Таджикистана, после приобретения Таджикистаном независимости. Здание имеет историческую ценность, именно здесь были приняты правовые акты по выпуску национальных валют Республики, сначала таджикский рубл (без мягкого знака в конце), а затем и нынешнюю национальную валюту - Сомони
Хочу работа на этот место
Экскурсия для детей в рамках недели финансовой грамотности
Судя по состоянию нашей банковской системы...

The botanic gardens are beautiful! Very well kept. I enjoyed the greenhouses too, such a variety of lovely plants. I can tell a lot of care goes in to looking after them. I wish there were some animals in the tropical house. Nice for an afternoon stroll.

Really blissful ..you can have a good walk here.
of course when the weather is good.. 
You can see a wide variety of flowers.. well maintained.

The Ulster museum at one corner for the park is definitely worth a visit...& there is no entry fee.
Wonderful gardens, and amazing hot houses. Beautifully set out.  And with the Ulster Museum on the grounds. Amazing.  All lovers of plant life, and Creation in general will enjoy time spent here.

Had a great day walking around the craft fair. Seen many spectacular flowers, massive vegetables and lots of stalls selling home made produces. The fudge was fantastic.

Found the Belfast ukelele jam group playing in a marquee. Wow great music.

Pleasant in the early Spring. The flowerbeds are full of vibrant colour. The hothouses are rich with blooms and scents. The lawns have not yet shaken off their winter rough and are damp, but not for long. The renovated tropical ravine is superb and the museum is nearby if it rains or you need a snack. If it's sunny, go and look at the herbacious borders; sit and listen to the bees at work.
A Restaurant in Dushanbe, providing Indian Cuisine. Good in serving snacks like Samosas, Jalebi. For meals, very good in Vegetables, Chaney,etc. but not in meat dishes.

Food is better as compared to tajik restaurants,
But not according to the prices,
Long wait but good meal.
Good Indian food !! Nice ambiance .worth for money..it take some good time to get your food !!
Desi food with prathas and much more.. especially onion patato pakoora and smoosa

The pineapple salsa was good, and I always love fried plantains... but everything else was okay at best. The mole lacked depth. The chips are like the cheap, hard kind you get at a grocery store. They’re definitely not made in house. Also $14 for 3 salsas and some chips is outrageous. I’d pass on it, if you’re looking for something spectacular.

Not your typical Mexican place! From the daily salsa list (try the strawberry salsa if you see it!) to lots of beautiful and flavorful specials, you'll find something to please your palate. If you have any questions about the dishes, the staff is quite willing to explain the menu and help you find the perfect plate. Oh, and the margaritas are top notch! It's a small place so we've found it best to go just after lunch. Note: They close at 4pm and reopen at 5pm.
Food is wonderful and well priced. The restaurant is quite small and gets full quickly, but  it is worth the wait. Service is rapid and overall, the restaurant is a great experience.

This place is amazing, they serve real delicious Mexican/Caribbean food. The waitresses and the cooks were on it, they were super nice and friendly. The wait was just a few mins. We enjoyed the food and will definitely recommend to anybody.

There was a little bit of a wait for 15 people but they did the best to accommodate us tonight. One of the best Mexican restaurants we have had and definitely worth the wait!! Thank you for the excellent service and food!!!
Delicious food! The staff was friendly and the ambiance was unique. I liked it!
Fabulous place to try authentic central asian food! Great food! Good people! Thumbs up! Thank you very much!🙏🏼
It was good i liked their food I just didnt like the entrance I though it was too creepy.

Great food, good atmosphere decent service. 
I have been there couple of times and the food has been consistently great. 
The problem around there is parking. There is absolutely no street parking around if you go there at wrong time. If you are around in the evening, good luck finding parking. 
Do not under estimate their kabobs. They are perfectly seasoned and juicy. 
The home made fruit punch is a must. 
If you want something cheap and filling, try their plov. It's very tasty and and filling and cheap.
Friendly atmosphere. Unfortunately, last time we attended this place, it was lacking service. Took a long time to order and then just as long to get the food.
(+) Good tomato soup and fresh vegetables salad, nice tea. The staff is friendly and professional. Convenient location, cozy atmosphere. Wi-Fi.

One of the few places in Dushanbe that carries international standards in terms of service. Not bad of a place, good looking staff and good food for a mid range price. I didn't enjoy the fresh juices and smoothies though, not the place for it.

Visited here back in March , cocktails were on the pricey side ( pricier than most bars in North America) , but the quality was pretty good . 
Servers seem to be insisting to speak English even tho I wanted to speak Farsi(Tajiki ) :))
Another thing that bugged me was there were too many servers and they almost watch all your move so of you need something they come and help out. This OS perefect but to a point not really a good feeling if they kinda watch you all the time .
Overall I will come back again but probably they should reduce the price abit ,
Nice place for lunch. Good internet connection is available
Very good place, with good service, delicious food, my best red velvate cake
